      • update

        public Subscriptions.UpdateInvocation update(java.lang.String library,
                                             java.lang.String subscription,
                                             SubscriptionsTypes.UpdateSpec spec)
        Description copied from interface: Subscriptions
        Updates the specified subscription of the published library.

        This is an incremental update to the subscription. Except for the SubscriptionsTypes.UpdateSpecPlacement class, properties that are null in the update specification will be left unchanged. If spec#subscribedLibraryPlacement is specified, all properties of the current subscribed library placement will be replaced by this placement.

        . This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.2.
        Specified by:
        update in interface Subscriptions
        Parameters:
        library - Identifier of the published library. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.content.Library.
        subscription - subscription identifier. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.content.library.Subscriptions.
        spec - Specification of the new property values to set on the subscription.
        Returns:
        instance of Subscriptions.UpdateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described update operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
